ng the impact on profits if a division accepts an external offer to buy a component, considering variable costs and fixed costs.\"", "\"QUIZ: TRANSFER PRICE FOR PROFIT MARGIN\":\"This quiz involves calculating the transfer price per unit that will result in a specified profit margin for a division, given the budgeted output and costs.\"", "\"OVERHEADS\":\"Overheads are the ongoing expenses of operating a business that are not directly attributed to specific business activities. They can be fixed or variable.\"", "\"TRANSFER PRICE PER UNIT\":\"Transfer price per unit = Total cost / (1 - Profit margin percentage)\"", "\"TRANSFER PRICING OBJECTIVES\":\"This quiz tests the understanding of the bases for setting a transfer price that results in goal congruent behavior by both the selling and receiving divisions.\"", "\"MINIMUM TRANSFER PRICE FOR DIVISION A\":\"This quiz involves calculating the minimum transfer price that Division A would accept for transferring Product S to Division B, considering external demand and opportunity costs.\"", "\"TRANSFER PRICING POLICY\":\"This quiz evaluates the objectives of a good transfer pricing system and whether a given transfer pricing policy achieves those objectives.\"", "\"IMPLEMENTATION AND EVALUATION OF EPOS AND ERPS IN XYZ STORES\":\"IMPLEMENTATION AND EVALUATION OF EPOS AND ERPS IN XYZ STORES\"\n\nXYZ Stores operates a chain of 10 convenience stores with basic information systems. The case involves the implementation and evaluation of Electronic Point of Sale (EPOS) and Enterprise Resource Planning Systems (ERPS) to improve operational efficiency.", "\"DIRECT LABOUR\":\"Direct labour\" refers to the wages and salaries of employees that can be directly attributed to the production of specific goods or services. It is a variable cost that increases by 3% every quarter to reflect the increase in sales volume. Additionally, in Q3, there is a one-off increase of $5,000 to account for training costs.", "\"ENTERPRISE RESOURCE PLANNING SYSTEM (ERPS)\":The Enterprise Resource Planning System (ERPS) is a comprehensive software system designed to facilitate a seamless flow of information across an entire organization. By utilizing a single database, it ensures that various programs used by different departments can access and share data efficiently. ERPS is an integrated information system that supports multiple simultaneous users, providing real-time information. It includes essential modules for accounting, inventory control, and other critical business processes, thereby enhancing the overall operational efficiency of the organization.", "\"REPORTING PROGRAMME\":\"A reporting programme is a software tool that analyzes data from the ERPS database and provides reports, summaries, and data visualizations such as bar charts, line charts, and pie charts. It includes a 'drill down' facility for detailed analysis and allows managers to design their own reports.\""], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-3-small", "temperature": 0.0, "frequency_penalty": null, "presence_penalty": null, "top_p": 1.0, "max_tokens": 4000, "n": 1}}